
Overview of verb reconstruct

The verb reconstruct has 5 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                    
1. (3) reconstruct, construct, retrace -- (reassemble mentally; "reconstruct the events of 20 years ago")
2. (1) rebuild, reconstruct -- (build again; "The house was rebuild after it was hit by a bomb")
3. (1) reconstruct -- (cause somebody to adapt or reform socially or politically)
4. restore, reconstruct -- (return to its original or usable and functioning condition; "restore the forest to its original pristine condition")
5. remodel, reconstruct, redo -- (do over, as of (part of) a house; "We are remodeling these rooms")
